<subSubSection id="C34C56E66249FFFB73872C51FD99FB47" pageId="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE9056D6249FFFB73872C51FD99FB47" blockId="19.[108,637,1075,1496]" pageId="19">
ETYMOLOGY: The new genus group name is a combination of 
<emphasis id="B922D97F6249FFFB721D2C37FEB4FBDB" box="[278,344,1109,1132]" italics="true" pageId="19">aporia</emphasis>
(Greek, meaning, “difficult” or “doubt”) and 
<emphasis id="B922D97F6249FFFB72212C17FE82FB3A" box="[298,366,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="19">cheilos</emphasis>
(Greek, “lip” or “rim”). Although the form of the name is technically a neuter plural, as is that of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C567EEE6249FFFB72BA2CD5FDFAFB78" box="[433,534,1207,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922D97F6249FFFB72BA2CD5FDFAFB78" box="[433,534,1207,1231]" italics="true" pageId="19">Megachile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<superScript id="7C23A8256249FFFB71172CD7FDC9FB71" attach="right" box="[540,549,1205,1222]" fontSize="7" pageId="19">2</superScript>
the gen- der of the name is here considered to be feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C56E66249FFFB73872C98FD9AFAA5" box="[140,630,1274,1298]" pageId="19" type="distribution">
